                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12902619" author="gdusbabek" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 20:40:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To prove that I&apos;m not hallucinating: &lt;a href=&quot;http://ci.apache.org/builders/cassandra-trunk/builds/437/steps/compile/logs/stdio&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://ci.apache.org/builders/cassandra-trunk/builds/437/steps/compile/logs/stdio&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12903611" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 27 Aug 2010 20:42:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this is caused by sstable statistics being written after the flush (see ssTableWriter.closeAndOpenReader)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is it time to admit that storing sstable info, in sstables, wasn&apos;t a good idea?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12903614" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 27 Aug 2010 20:44:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(this isn&apos;t just a test issue, i&apos;m pretty sure it could bork drain, too)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12903675" author="gdusbabek" created="Fri, 27 Aug 2010 22:20:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;is it time to admit that storing sstable info, in sstables, wasn&apos;t a good idea?&lt;br/&gt;
What if statistics operations ran on its own stage that could be halted at critical moments (flushing, for example).&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12903689" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 27 Aug 2010 22:33:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it already feels like a rather ugly set of workarounds, and maybe it&apos;s time to cut our losses&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12903693" author="gdusbabek" created="Fri, 27 Aug 2010 22:43:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t disagree.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1382&quot; title=&quot;Race condition leads to FileNotFoundException on startup&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1382&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1382&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should be on the list of things that get reverted when we figure out a better way of statistics.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12903697" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 27 Aug 2010 22:57:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s just create an EstimatedHistogram serializer and write out one for each of the row sizes and column counts.  SSTable.components will have to be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906161" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 3 Sep 2010 23:04:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to remove sstable stats from the system table, and make them their own sstable component.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906194" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 4 Sep 2010 00:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m getting build errors in a couple test classes&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906199" author="brandon.williams" created="Sat, 4 Sep 2010 01:08:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oops, I&apos;d forgotten about more tests being added due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1155&quot; title=&quot;keep persistent row statistics&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1155&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1155&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s problems.  Patch updated to fix tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906206" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 4 Sep 2010 01:29:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906215" author="brandon.williams" created="Sat, 4 Sep 2010 03:32:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906572" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 6 Sep 2010 19:30:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this broke StreamingTransferTest (easy to miss in the ant output because it is a timeout rather than a failure)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906619" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 6 Sep 2010 22:51:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1471&quot; title=&quot;Improve SSTable discovery and allow for more components&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1471&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1471&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12908543" author="hudson" created="Sun, 12 Sep 2010 19:39:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #533 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/533/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/533/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
